# Neovim

- For Neovim plugin/maintenance ops (Lazy update/sync, `Mason`/`MasonInstall`,
  `TSInstall`, `checkhealth`, …), prefer `nvim --headless "<commands>" "+qa"` over
  asking the user to run them interactively inside Neovim.
- Headless runs are scriptable and deterministic — capture the output, assert success,
  and don't leave an interactive session open.
